ible for a star to shine and not get noticed, even in the dark.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nIt's incredible how nature sets females up to take care of people, and yet it is tricky for them to take care of themselves.\n\n- Björk\n|\nWhen you discover your gift and develop it, the world will start looking for you\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhy wait to get old and dream about the things you could have done, when you can start now and look back on the things you did.\n\n- Allan\n|\nThe only relevance worth to pursue, is living your passion through your interests.\n\n- Unarine\n|\nFor ourselves, who are ordinary men and women, let us return thanks to Nature for her bounty by using every one of the senses she has given us.\n\n- Virginia Woolf, The Common Reader\n|\nThe extent of God’s grace always eclipses the extent of my grotesqueness. Therefore, I can never be bad enough for God to tell me that He’s had enough.\n\n- Craig\n|\nIt’s your call. You want to go back home, go ahead. But if I were you, I wouldn’t. Home is death.\n\n- Jeff Abbott, Panic\n|\nMost aspects of my training didn’t agree with me. There wasn’t as much bossing around as I’d hoped for, and there was way too much following orders.\n\n- Rachel Vincent, Rogue\n|\nWe have grace of strength to work, to clear our cities of any dirt.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nThe eye through which I see God is the same eye through which God sees me; my eye and God's eye are one eye, one seeing, one knowing, one love.\n\n- Meister Eckhart, Sermons of Meister Eckhart\n|\nLord, please do this ... or do something better!\n\n- Priscilla Shirer, God is Able\n|\nI am a man of peace [so he told Mother, but it always appeared to me that he was the most belligerent man of peace I had ever encountered]\n\n- Howard Fast, April Morning\n|\nI have things in my head that are not like what anyone taught me — shapes and ideas so near to me, so natural to my way of being and thinking.\n\n- Georgia\n|\nSomehow, we'll find it. The balance between whom we wish to be and whom we